# Project general coding standards

- Never use emojis.
- Keep the code clean and readable.
- Keep comments short and concise.
- Avoid redundant comments and pieces of code.
- Avoid filler in conversation, stick to the essential.
- If the user asks for something ambiguous, ask for clarification before proceeding.
- Avoid beeing overly assertive in your responses, don't claim facts unless verifiable and verified.
- If uncertain about an outcome, be transparent in your response and provide way to verify if possible.